    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-10-28T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-10-28T03:00:00-05:00" n="696"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d696">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/13242: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Counselor of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lockhart</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-10-28T16:00:00+08:00"
                            >October 28, 1935—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 28—9:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>99. Embassy’s 93, October 26, 5 p.m.<note n="16" xml:id="d696fn16">Not
                        printed.</note> Party of 23 foreign missionaries from Lanchow arrived safely
                    in Peiping this morning. The following 11 Americans were included in the party:
                    Miss Ruth Lindstrom, Miss Anna Haupberg, Mr. and Mrs. Calvin Snyder, Mr. and
                    Mrs. Charles Notson, and Mr. and Mrs. Francis Derk and their three children.
                    Repeated to Nanking, Shanghai and Hankow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lockhart</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
